Another approach might be to use try/catch instead. It&#39;s a bit untidy but from what I understand this test is going to be short-lived anyway as it&#39;s for TDD:

    @Test
    public void testNPENotThrown{
      Calling calling= Mock(Calling.class);
      testClass.setInner(calling);
      testClass.setThrow(true);
        
      try{
        testClass.testMethod();
